abstract: CINCINNATI, Ohio, Dec. 4.--At 1:30 o' clock this morning Henry Lammerding, a bar-tender for Jake Aug, a Vine-street saloon-keeper, was fatally shot by Charlie Beck. Beck entered Aug's clubhouse and asked for a drink. Lammerding refused to give it to him for the reason that he had taken enough. Beck thereupon drew a pistol and shot Lammerding twice. Lammerding is still alive and may recovor. Beck has been arrested.
